Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Put the sliced pepper onto a #baking tray{} and drizzle with @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until soft and slightly charred, ~{14-16%minutes}.

While the pepper cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #medium frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Drain the @king prawns{225%grams}.

Once hot, add the prawns. Stir-fry until the prawns are cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw prawns. Cook so they're opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Add the garlic and @peri peri seasoning{1%sachet} to the prawns. Fry for ~{1%minute}.

While the prawns cooks, trim the @iceberg lettuce{1/2}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%grams}.

In a #small bowl{}, mix together the @mayonnaise{3%tbsp} and @sweet chilli sauce{32%grams}.

A couple of mins before you're ready to serve, pop the @plain taco tortillas{6} onto a baking tray and into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

When everything's ready, lay the tortillas onto your serving plates (3 per person).

To make your tacos, spread the base of each with sweet chilli mayo, top with the lettuce, charred pepper and peri peri prawns.

Finish with your grated cheese. Enjoy!